{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"run-atom-drawl","description":"# Merge G3+G4 into one container call per bin (2N -> N)\n\n## Why\nG3 (child-coverage) and G4 (child-consistency) share the identical (parent, child, roster) context and are\ndisjoint audits the container prompt already describes together. Evaluating both in one call halves container\ncalls (2N -> N).\n\n## What\n- Evaluate G3 AND G4 in ONE call per (child/bin): present both rubrics over the shared context (`passes.py` +\n  `plan_review_container.md`). Keep per-criterion attribution in the output (findings tagged G3 vs G4).\n- Gate behind an OFFLINE EVAL confirming combined-call findings match separate-call findings within tolerance\n  (two rubrics in one turn must not dilute either).\n\n## Scope\n- In: the merged G3+G4 container call + attribution + the offline eval.\n- Out: parallelization (S3, dependency); bin-packing (S5).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] G3 and G4 are evaluated in one call per bin; findings are correctly attributed to G3 vs G4.\n- [ ] An offline eval shows no accuracy regression vs separate G3/G4 calls (within tolerance).\n- [ ] Container call count halves (2N -> N) for an epic; `make lint` + tests pass.\n","id":"98c6-81c7-175e-416f","parent_id":"c81c-cbcd-17a0-43d2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Merge G3+G4 into one container call per bin (2N -> N)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782543575157651001,"uuid":"92112c6a-7d5b-4fdb-af24-bbe90767e68a"}